NASA FIRMS data shows that large fires are burning in Znamyanka, Kirovohrad Oblast, after it was hit by at least 6 Geran-2 drones during last night's strikes. 
The targets were the locomotive depot and the train station. Ukrzaliznytsia announced widespread train delays in numerous regions due to "damage to railway infrastructure". 
Locomotive depot: 48.713482, 32.663084
Railway station: 48.710409, 32.704414

NASA FIRMS data shows that a large fire is burning at Branch No. 1 of the state enterprise "Spetsoboronmash", in eastern Zhytomyr near the border with Kyiv Oblast. Spetsoboronmash specialises in production of explosives, ammunition, air and space vehicles, other electrical equipment, and related equipment.
~3 Kalibr cruise missiles impacted it.

Today, a video appeared and was widely published showing a Ukrainian soldier pretending to be a Russian soldier, before turning and shooting the two Russians he was walking with. 
People have already begun to show this area as under full Ukrainian control, but obviously this is not the case. Sentinel satellite imagery shows that the frontline in this area remains largely the same, but further imagery set to be published tomorrow should clear up any remaining doubts. 
For the past 10 days, Ukrainian DRGs have been operating deep behind Russian lines in the entire bulge between Pokrovsk and Kostyantynivka. There aren't many of them - far less than Russia's DRG operations last month - but they are still present in a few different areas, aiming to disrupt Russian supply and consolidation efforts. 
As of now, the line of contact runs through the middle of Nykanorivka, south of Dorozhnje, and southeast of Bilytske. The video was recorded around 4.4km from the closest Ukrainian positions.
